Clone this repository to a local subdirectory:

@example sh
git clone https://git.sr.ht/~mew/kixtart-mode
@end example

Within the Emacs configuration, add the path of the cloned directory
to the value of @code{load-path}.  The following example assumes that
the repository was cloned within a directory named "manual-packages"
within the user's ".emacs.d" directory:

@example lisp
(add-to-list 'load-path "~/.emacs.d/manual-packages/kixtart-mode")
@end example
